defaultIntroduction and Backgrounddefault1.default This submission is based on the experiences of a team of academics based in Northern Ireland. They are members of the Ulster Business School's Department of Business &amp; Enterprise, University of Ulster. The response is based on 
defaultdata collected as part of an
default on-
defaultgoing doctoral research study into Northern Ireland’s property market. The aim of the study is to explore the causes and consequences of the recent property market bubble in Northern Ireland. 
default2. defaultOne aspect of the study involved examining the banking s
defaultector in Northern Ireland. In particular, evidence was gathered regarding the structure of the decision making processes adopted by the banks in Northern Ireland in relation to lending, in particular mortgage lending. Data was gathered on the changes in th
defaulte operations and policies of banks in Northern Ireland in recent years. To achieve this, semi structured interviews were conducted with a range of key stakeholders in the study, including banks and property developers. This was complemented by secondary 
defaultco
defaultntent
default analysis
default.
default 
default3.default Five banks that currently operate in Northern Ireland have participated in the study and findings have been triangulated within each participant organisation.
default 
defaultFor competitive reasons the identity of these organisations has been 
defaultanonymi
defaultsed
default.
default4. defaultThe main reason for submitting a response is because the primary evidence gathered as part of this study contributes to the debate and the inquiry into the banking structure in Northern Ireland.
